      • Pet

        public Pet​(java.lang.String name,
           java.lang.String type,
           double age,
           double weight,
           double height,
           Person owner)
        Constructor method for class Pet which is a pet offered by the veterinary.
        Parameters:
        name - The pet's name. This param must not be empty.
        type - The pet's species. This param can only be "Dog", "Cat", "Bird" or "Other". It won't get any other String.
        age - The pet's age. This param must be greater than zero.
        weight - The pet's weight. This param must be greater than zero.
        height - The pet's height. This param must be greater than zero.
        owner - The person (object) who is the pet's owner. This param must not be null.

      • calculateBmi

        public double calculateBmi()
        This method allows to calculate the body mass index for a pet.
        pre: The pet was created before and its attributes height and weight are not null neither height must be zero.
        post: The BMI is calculated.
        Returns:
        The pet body mass index (BMI).
        Throws:
        If - the height is zero, so an exception is thrown due to the division on zero does not exist.

      • addMedicine

        public java.lang.String addMedicine​(java.lang.String medsName,
                                    double medsDose,
                                    double medsPrice,
                                    java.lang.String medsFrecuency)
        This method allows to add new medicines that were prescription during the hospitalization at the patient stories.
        pre: The patient clinic story must be not null.
        post: New medicines were added to the patient clinic story.
        Parameters:
        medsName - The medicine name. This param must be not null.
        medsDose - The medicine dose, this param refers to the amount of medicine supplied to the pet each time according the frequence assigned. This param must be not null.
        medsPrice - The medicine cost by each dose. This param could be empty.
        medsFrecuency - The frequency of medicine application. This param could be empty.
        Returns:
        A message that indiques if medicine was added to the patient clinic story
